<DOC><DOCNO> AP890228-0151 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-02-28-89 2054EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Nicaragua-Honduras     02-28 0125</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Nicaragua-Honduras,0128</SECOND><HEAD>Nicaragua Accuses Honduras of Border Attacks</HEAD><HEAD>With AM-Nicaragua</HEAD><DATELINE>MANAGUA, Nicaragua (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The government claimed Wednesday thatHonduran soldiers fired on Nicaraguan border posts 13 times thisyear.   A Defense Ministry statement said the latest incident was amortar attack Sunday on the Murupuchi outpost in Nuevo Segoviaprovince, 110 miles north of Managua. It did not mention casualties.   On Monday, the ministry accused Honduran troops of firing threetimes last week on posts near Teotecancinte, also in Nueva Segovia.That report also said nothing about casualties.   Honduras did not comment immediately, but such charges are commonand consistently denied.   About 11,000 Nicaraguan rebels live with their families in campsjust inside Honduran and their presence has increased tension alongthe frontier.</TEXT></DOC>